Short, one-page entries in which Cole records his daily interactions with friends and family including his father, engraver Timothy Cole, and his wife, sculptor Margaret Ward Cole ("Madge"); his visits to the Salmagundi Club, the Allied Artists of America, and teaching at Cooper Union; and descriptions of the paintings he is working on, primarily portraits.
Blank pages not scanned.
This is one of 70 diaries in the Alphaeus P. Cole papers kept by Cole between 1889-1982.
Archives of American Art, Smithsonian Institution
